The '''Representative Office of Palestine''' in the [[Germany|Federal Republic of Germany]] ({{lang-ar|سفارة دولة فلسطين لدى ألمانيا}}) is the [[diplomatic mission]] of the [[State of Palestine|Palestine]] in Germany. It is located in [[Berlin]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mofa.pna.ps/ar/archives/3272|title=Embassy of the State of Palestine in Germany|publisher=Ministry of foreign affairs of State of Palestine|accessdate=25 June 2017}}</ref> The [[East Germany|German Democratic Republic]] (GDR, East Germany) recognized the State of Palestine in 1988 prior to the [[German reunification]] in 1990 with [[West Germany]] although the current government does not recognize the State of Palestine.

